A Chilean television channel has come under fire after a broadcasting the moment when a teenage boy was shot dead by police.

The 16-year-old boy had stolen a car in San Bernardo, south Chile, and a policeman on motorcycle chased him down the road and shot him. 

Viewers have hit out at both the local TV channel and police, who, they say, crossed the line when they shot the young boy.

