The video was recorded on the police officer's helmet camera, and shows him asking the driver to stop the vehicle several times.

The police officer is then seen firing his handgun repeatedly at the driver's side of the car before rushing over.

The camera then films  the bloodstained teenager lying slumped forward and not moving.

The 16-year-old was still alive when ambulance arrived, but later died in hospital.

The video was broadcast on a show called 'Criminal Gangs', where it quickly went viral after being shared on social networks.

